     CDS             1..495
                     /label="NusA"
                     /synonym="nusA"
                     /synonym="N-utilization substance protein A"
                     /synonym="transcription termination/antitermination protein
                     NusA"
                     /note="E. coli K-12 NusA (N-utilization substance protein
                     A), 495 aa, UniProt P0AFF6. Essential transcription
                     elongation factor that enhances transcriptional pausing and
                     intrinsic termination; displaced from RNAP by sigma at
                     initiation. Multi-domain architecture: NTD (aa 1–137,
                     interacts with RNAP beta-flap tip helix), S1 RNA-binding
                     domain, KH RNA-binding domain, AR1 (interacts with
                     bacteriophage lambda N antiterminator), AR2
                     (autoinhibitory). Also widely deployed as an N-terminal
                     solubility-enhancing fusion tag in recombinant protein
                     expression."
